.TH "seccomp_attach_filter" 9 "seccomp_attach_filter" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
seccomp_attach_filter \- validate and attach filter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" seccomp_attach_filter
.BI "(unsigned int flags "  ","
.BI "struct seccomp_filter *filter "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "flags" 12
flags to change filter behavior
.IP "filter" 12
seccomp filter to add to the current process
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Caller must be holding current->sighand->siglock lock.

Returns 0 on success, -ve on error, or
- in TSYNC mode: the pid of a thread which was either not in the correct
seccomp mode or did not have an ancestral seccomp filter
- in NEW_LISTENER mode: the fd of the new listener
